      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REGGAE ETHICS (2) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish 2.25 lengths away in second (22.41) at Maitland in a Grade 5 over 400m. Has a very good strike-rate from this draw, with four wins from five starts. Can measure up this time. SASSY CROSSED (1) finds it hard to win. Finished in the minors latest when second (19.51) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Can feature again. MYSTICAL ETHICS (8) is first up since finishing fourth (25.84) in a Grade 5 at Maitland over 450m three-and-a-half months ago. Tends to go well off this box draw. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. SHADY COYOTE (7) warrants respect although new to this track.",
